text: L6.10. MRU Cache Replacement Assume you are given a tiny 4-element, fully-associative cache that uses MRU replacement. The cache stores single byte values (i.e., a line is a single byte). If the cache is empty at the beginning of execution, how many misses will the following string of accesses produce? B,E,E,B,E,A,B,A,A,A,E,C,G,G,A,E,G,A,A,B integer misses @ Save & Grade Single attempt Additional attempts available with new variants @
